  "prompt": "How much does an IAS earn in hand for services?",
  "response": "The salary of an Indian Administrative Service (IAS) officer varies based on their rank, experience, and posting, as well as the implementation of various pay commissions. As of the 7th Pay Commission, the basic pay for an IAS officer starts at around \u20b956,100 per month at the entry-level (Junior Scale) and can go significantly higher with promotions.\n\nAfter including allowances such as the Dearness Allowance (DA), House Rent Allowance (HRA), and other benefits, the in-hand salary for a newly appointed IAS officer can be approximately \u20b970,000 to \u20b980,000 per month, depending on the city and specific allowances applicable.\n\nFor senior IAS officers, the salary can increase to a few lakhs per month, especially for those in higher positions or those who are serving in important administrative roles.\n\nPlease note that these figures can change due to policy revisions or new pay commissions, so it\u2019s advisable to consult the latest government notifications for the most accurate and updated figures.",
